docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3248:The practical recommendation is to keep GlyphWeave grids **under ~15×15 cells** for reliable LLM generation, use modular composition of pre-defined blocks rather than freeform generation, and design patterns that avoid counting-dependent repetition (e.g., distinctive motifs over runs of identical characters).
docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3274:The **CP437 character set** remains the foundational "modular motif kit" of the traditional text art world, with the Dwarf Fortress tileset community (dozens of 16×16 grid tilesets corresponding to CP437's 256 positions) representing the most developed sprite kit tradition. REXPaint's .xp format, with import libraries in 10+ languages (Rust, Python, JavaScript, Swift, Haxe, Java, Nim, C#, Lua, SFML), is the most interoperable modular text art format.
docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3276:For licensing, precedent points toward a **dual model**: art/motif assets under CC BY 4.0 (following Twemoji) or CC BY-SA 4.0 (following OpenMoji's model as the strongest precedent for community-driven creative assets), code/tools under MIT, and any font components under SIL Open Font License 1.1 (the industry standard, celebrating its 20th anniversary in November 2025).
docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3431:| 30% | Use of Medium | Leverages hybrid ASCII+emoji nature; not just one or the other; exploits grid, palettes, motifs | 1-10 |
docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3487:| GW-012 | Implement model experiment logging with full telemetry. For every generation attempt, log to PostgreSQL: timestamp, model_id, effort_level, temperature, prompt_text (plan phase + generate phase), raw_llm_output, generated_code, sandbox_execution_time_ms, validation_passes (list of pass/fail per check), retry_count, retry_error_messages, final_art_output, assessment_scores, assessment_model, total_pipeline_time_ms, token_count_estimate, cost_estimate. Provide query functions for the experiment dashboard: per-model aggregates, time-series of scores, comparison matrices. | MUST | T2 | - Every generation attempt logged with all fields<br/>- Failed attempts logged too (for success rate calculation)<br/>- Query by model returns aggregate statistics<br/>- Time-series query returns score progression<br/>- Comparison matrix: model × art_type with avg scores<br/>- Logs queryable from gallery dashboard<br/>- Cost estimates computed from model registry pricing |
docs/discovery_20260329_092950.md:3559:The practical recommendation is to keep GlyphWeave grids **under ~15×15 cells** for reliable LLM generation, use modular composition of pre-defined blocks rather than freeform generation, and design patterns that avoid counting-dependent repetition (e.g., distinctive motifs over runs of identical characters).
