sdp/cypherclaw-v2-design-statement-2026-05-22.md:210:   - **Implementation suggestion:** the composer pre-computes contour position (climax/ascending/descending/static) per note and passes a `dynamics_multiplier` and `attack_shape` per OSC event. No model required.
sdp/cypherclaw-v2-design-statement-2026-05-22.md:213:   - **Implementation suggestion:** a single shared "affective state" float per voice family on a control bus. When voice A's recent expression intensity rises, the bus value rises; other voices' gesture parameters read this bus and modulate accordingly (e.g., vibrato rate × (1 + 0.5×affect_bus)).
sdp/cypherclaw-v2-design-statement-2026-05-22.md:217:   - **Implementation suggestion:** per-voice rolling-window intensity counter (last ~8 bars). When high, applies a damping multiplier to max amplitude and vibrato depth. Silence and soft passages decay it toward 0.
my-claw/sdp/prd-publication-and-gallery-surfaces.md:19:| PGS-003 | Implement explicit publish controls for broader exposure. Publish must be a separate action from normal home creation or federation enrollment. | MUST | T1 | - Operator can promote a gallery from private to public intentionally<br/>- Publish action is auditable<br/>- Unpublish returns the page to private access |
