sdp/verification/t-023@20260427t001208zc-verify.md:88:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-27T05:34:01.677Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777268041677_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-023 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-023_20260427T001208Zc_1777267925.log\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-26\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/request.py`\n- `tests/test_generation_request.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/composer_hook.py`\n- `tests/test_generation_composer_hook.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sample_selector.py`\n- `tests/test_sample_selector.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of the content hash in `GenerationRequest` is correct and deterministic. It uses a versioned header (\"GenerationRequest:v1\") and includes all relevant generation fields (prompt, clap_centroid, duration, seed, model, bpm_target) while correctly excluding the `backend` field. This ensures that the same request content results in the same hash regardless of which backend is used for execution.\n\n## Completeness\nThe task requirements were fully met. Both the existing `GenerationRequest` tests and the new hash tests pass. Coverage includes:\n- Equality and hashing of `GenerationRequest` objects.\n- Content hash stability across backends.\n- Content hash sensitivity to all generation parameters.\n- Deterministic request building in the composer hook.\n- \"Generated\" source selection logic in the sample selector.\n\n## Consistency\nThe new tests and implementation follow the established patterns in the codebase. Use of `struct` for deterministic binary encoding in the hash function is consistent with high-integrity hashing requirements. The test naming and structure align with existing test modules.\n\n## Security\nNo security issues were identified. Hashing is used for caching/identification, not for cryptographic secrets.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is well-structured and follows Python best practices. The hash function is robust against field collisions by using length-prefixing. Tests are comprehensive and cover both success and error cases (e.g., validation logic in `GenerationRequest`).\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] No regressions found in the relevant modules.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe full test suite (3713 items) was run. While some environment-specific issues were encountered (related to macOS Seatbelt restrictions and numba caching), these were bypassed using temporary redirects (`PROMPTCLAW_PETS_FILE` and `NUMBA_CACHE_DIR`). All 3710 collected tests passed (with 3 intentional skips). The specific tests for T-023 passed cleanly.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-023 @20260427t001208zc-verify.md"}}
